Regulations under section 13
Those regulations which are of only temporary effect are not reproduced.
THE STATISTICS (FOREST INDUSTRIES) REGULATIONS
1. These Regulations may be cited as the Statistics (Forest Industries) Regulations.
2. In these Regulations, except where the context otherwise requires -
"boardmilling" means converting any timber to boards wider than three feet by mechanical, semi-mechanical or chemical means;
"furniture making" means manufacturing furniture from round, sawn or processed timber;
"other wood industry" means any wood-using industry not herein defined;
"person in charge", in relation to any undertaking, means the person who, whether as owner, agent or manager, controls or manages the undertaking;
"pitsawing" means converting round timber to sawn timber by means of a hand saw;
"processed timber" means timber of which the natural physical structure has been changed by mechanical, semi-mechanical or chemical means;
"pulpmiliing" means converting timber to pulp by mechanical semi-mechanical or chemical means;
"resawing" means converting square or semi-square timber into sawn timber;
"round timber" means felled trees, logs, or poles;
"sawmilling" means converting round timber to sawn timber by mechanical or semi-mechanical means;
"undertaking" means any trade or business engaged, whether solely or in connexion with any other activity, in boardmilling, furniture making, pitsawing, pulpmilling, resawing, sawmilling or other wood industry; and where any undertaking has a separate establishment or establishments, each establishment of that undertaking shall be deemed, for the purpose of these Regulations, to be a separate undertaking.
3. (1) The person in charge of any undertaking may be required by an authorized officer to make a return containing the particulars and information specified in the Schedule in respect of the undertaking.
(2) For the purposes of any return required by this regulation, forms on which the return so required shall be made may be prepared and distributed by authorized officers, and every person required to make a return under these Regulations shall do so on those forms.
4. Any person required by an authorized officer to make a return under regulation 3 shall do so within fifteen days of the date on which
he received the forms or within such longer period as the authorized officer requiring the return to be made may allow.
5. All returns made under these Regulations shall be made to the Director of Statistics, Central Bureau of Statistics, P.O. Box 30266,
Nairobi.
6. An authorized officer may require any person who has made any return under these Regulations to supply him, whether by answering questions or otherwise as the officer sees fit, with such further information as may, in the opinion of the officer, be necessary to enable him to ascertain whether the matters and particulars stated in
that person's return are fully and accurately furnished.

