5.The pilot census, national census and the post-census survey shall be conducted by the Director of Statistics under the guidance of the National Census Steering Committee, which shall consist of -
(a) the Provincial Commissioner, Nairobi who shall be the chairman of the committee and the National Census Officer;
(b) the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Planning and National Development who shall be the alternate chairman;
(c) the Director of Planning in the Ministry of Planning and National Development;
(d) the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Finance or his representative,
(e) the Director of National Council for Population and Development;
(f) the Director of Survey of Kenya;
(g) the Director of Population Studies and Research Institute, University of Nairobi;
(h) the Director of the Department of Resources Survey and Remote Sensing of the Ministry of Planning and National Development;
(i) the Director of Housing in the Ministry of Public Works;
(j) the Director of Labour in the Ministry of Labour;
(k) the Director of Education in the Ministry of Education and Human Resource Development;
(I) the Secretary-General of the Kenya Union of Journalists;
(m) a representative of the Department of Personnel Management in the Office of the President;
(n) the technical advisers; and
(o) the project co-ordinator who shall also be the secretary to the committee.
(p)one official of the following organisations who is based in the district to represent each of the following persons respectively -
(i) the Secretary-General of (lie Kenya Association of Manufacturers;
(ii) the Director of the Federation of Kenya Employers;
(iii) the Secretary-General of the Kenya National Union of Teachers;
(iv) the National Chairperson of Maendeleo ya Wanawake
(v) the Secretary-General of the Central Organization of Trade Unions;
(q) one person based in the district to represent the local branch of each of the following organizations respectively -
(i) The national council of Non- Governmental organizations;
(ii) the National Council of Churches of Kenya;
(iii) the Kenya Catholic Secretariat;
(iv) the Evangelical Fellowship of Kenya; and
(v) the Supreme Council of Kenya Muslims.

