5. DEFINITIONS
(a) "Kenya citizen" means any person who is a citizen of Kenya under the Constitution of Kenya and does not include any person who has applied for citizenship but has not yet been issued with the appropriate certificate of registration or naturalization.
(b) "Employee" includes any person in receipt of remuneration from his employment or whether as a director, manager, agent or casual labourer or otherwise, but does not include a sole business proprietor or any consular, trade or other representative of a foreign government
or members of the armed forces.
(c) "Wholly owned by Kenya citizens" means 100 per cent owned by Kenya citizens;
(d) "Mainly owned by Kenya citizens" means where Kenya citizens own more than 50 per cent but less than 100 per cent of the business;
(e) "Family worker" means any person actively engaged in the daily operation of a business without receiving a regular wage or salary, but does not include a business proprietor or a director, manager, agent or partner who is not a member of the family;
(f) "Self-employed person" means any individual engaged in a business of which he is the owner or in which he is a partner.
6. COMPLETION AND RETURN OF FORM
Please answer all questions and return this form before 30th November, 1986 (the extra copy is for your records). If necessary you should use reasonable estimates rather than wait for fully audited figures. If for any reason you will not be able to return the form by this date, please inform the Central Bureau of Statistics immediately.

